cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.CE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it focuses on modeling the information diffusion process in online social networks. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) as it involves developing a theoretical framework for measuring and predicting the density of influenced users. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it deals with analyzing social networks and their behavior. The paper also involves data analysis and modeling, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
